00:01:08.970 --> 00:01:11.010
But that isn't the way the world was always
imagined.

00:01:11.010 --> 00:01:14.900
So there's an argument to be made that all
of these communities in the eastern Mediterranean

00:01:14.900 --> 00:01:19.640
-- what historians sometimes call the Levant
or the Ancient Near East, because it is closer

00:01:19.640 --> 00:01:23.840
to Britain than it is the Far East -- these
days we often call it the Mid East. It's almost

00:01:23.840 --> 00:01:28.110
as though there is no actual "East" and "West"
on the globe.

00:01:28.110 --> 00:01:31.920
Anyway, you can make the argument that back
